         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden ¶ 8/10/72 ¶  ¶ The Case with Euphorbiaceae, dear Mr Bentham, has come back to me in perfect safety since last I wrote. The anxieties in my almost upset Department leave me no res...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.10.08</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew Correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1871-1881, f. 65.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">8/10/72</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Case with <name key="Euphorbiaceae">Euphorbiaceae</name>, dear Mr Bentham, has come back to me in perfect safety since last I wrote. The anxieties in my almost upset Department leave me no rest to write to you just now at length.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am exceedingly pleased with the progress of the work, and as the <name key="Orchideae">Orchideae</name> are on their way to you by the "Somersetshire"-Steamer you will not be hindered or delayed. Should the <name key="Orchideae">Orchideae</name> not prove sufficient for finishing the volume, then I will at once send off the <name key="Haemodoraceae">Haemodoraceae</name> and any other orders you may wish to include. Should I not write again, then let me ask now already, that my Baronial Rank may be recognized on the title page. I simply ask this for 2 reasons. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>1. its omission might throw a doubt on its genu[e]ness. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>2. because it is hereditary and I have reason to think it will aid in brightening my future and make me independent by the alliance with an influencial and independent family.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The family has not been identified. This letter was written three years after a previous fiancée, Rebecca Nordt, had married Arthur Moule (Brown-May &amp; Maroske, 1994). See also Lucas (2013a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With grateful remembrance of all your goodness and with my best wishes for your health and happiness</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">In letters from the Duke of Buckingham, Earl Granville, also from the Duke of Argylls Department<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The India Office (Cook &amp; Keith (1975))<seg style="">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> my title is fully acknowledged<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See, for example, Lord Granville to M, 8 December 1871, and the Duke of Buckingham to M, 9 December 1871.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
